"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. You know I'm an avid gardener, and my crop, uh my fall, hot summer crop is going off. And as it begins to really produce heavy with the ochre and eggplant and all these things, you have to think about how to preserve your food so you're not just producing a whole bunch during harvest and then not eating it all year. So fermentation, turning things into sauces, using oils. This is a great way to preserve your food, and it's something everyone should be doing if you are gardening. If you're interested in this subject, uh September 13th in Houston, Texas at Wabash Feed and Garden, I'm going to be giving a little talk on food preservation from the garden, and we're going to be using a bunch of the local stuff that is going very well here, the eggplants and the okras and all the hot weather stuff, the long beans and everything else that we have there that's just flourishing, but it's all the hot stuff. So we're gonna be doing some food preservation, some fermentation. Come on down September 13th at Wabash Feed and Garden. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.96,\n      \"end\": 2.08,\n      \"duration\": 1.12,\n      \"confidence\": 0.98,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.2,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.993\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 1.2,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.44,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"s